---
import BaseLayout from "../../layout/BaseLayout.astro";
import teaPlatformImage from "../../assets/images/tea-platform.png";

const seo = {
	title: "TEA Platform | CVD-Net Resources",
	description:
		"Information about the TEA Platform resource from the CVD-Net project.",
};
---

<BaseLayout seo={seo}>
	<div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12">
		<div class="mb-12 text-center">
			<h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold lg:text-5xl">TEA Platform</h1>
			<div class="mb-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2">
				<a
					href="https://github.com/alan-turing-institute/AssurancePlatform"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					<img
						src="https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-TEA_Platform-blue?logo=github"
						alt="GitHub Repository"
					/>
				</a>
				<a
					href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8198986"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					<img
						src="https://zenodo.org/badge/DOI/10.5281/zenodo.8198986.svg"
						alt="DOI"
					/>
				</a>
				<a
					href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					<img
						src="https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg"
						alt="License: MIT"
					/>
				</a>
				<a
					href="https://app.travis-ci.com/alan-turing-institute/AssurancePlatform"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					<img
						src="https://app.travis-ci.com/alan-turing-institute/AssurancePlatform.svg?branch=MVP"
						alt="Build Status"
					/>
				</a>
				<a
					href="https://assuranceplatform.azurewebsites.net/"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					<img
						src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Go%20to%20the%20TEA%20Platform-0F76B8?style=flat"
						alt="Go to the TEA Platform"
					/>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="mb-10">
			<img
				src={teaPlatformImage.src}
				alt="TEA Platform hero image"
				class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
			/>
		</div>

		<div class="mx-auto">
			<p class="mb-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
				The Trustworthy and Ethical Assurance (TEA) platform, developed
				by researchers at The Alan Turing Institute and University of
				York, is an open-source, community-focused initiative. It's
				designed to help anyone involved in creating or using
				data-driven technologies – from developers to the public –
				confidently demonstrate that these technologies uphold important
				ethical principles like fairness, explainability, or safety. The
				platform tackles the complex challenge of how project teams can
				provide clear, justified evidence that such principles have been
				considered and met throughout a technology's entire lifecycle,
				from initial design to deployment.
			</p>

			<p class="mb-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
				The TEA platform offers a systematic way to address these
				challenges through three core components. Firstly, the <strong
					>TEA Tool</strong
				> is an interactive, graphical software that helps teams build "assurance
				cases." Think of an assurance case as a structured argument, clearly
				showing the ethical goals of a technology, the specific properties
				that support these goals, and the evidence backing up these claims.
				Secondly, the <strong>TEA Framework</strong> provides learning resources
				and guidance, making the process of creating these assurance cases
				more accessible to people from various backgrounds, regardless of
				their technical expertise.
			</p>

			<p class="mb-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
				Finally, the <strong>TEA Community</strong> fosters collaboration
				and shared learning. Developing ethical technology is not a solo
				effort; it benefits immensely from diverse perspectives. The community
				aspect helps in identifying key ethical concerns, sharing best practices
				and examples, collectively evaluating the strength of assurance arguments,
				and continuously improving the TEA platform itself. By bringing together
				these tools, resources, and a collaborative environment, the TEA
				platform aims to make the development and communication of trustworthy
				and ethical technology more robust, transparent, and inclusive.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-700">
				Key Components
			</h2>
			<ul class="mb-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-lg text-slate-600">
				<li>
					<strong>TEA Tool</strong>: Interactive software for building
					structured assurance cases
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>TEA Framework</strong>: Learning resources and
					guidance for creating effective assurance cases
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>TEA Community</strong>: Collaborative environment
					for sharing knowledge and best practices
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-700">
				Resources & Access
			</h2>
			<p class="mb-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
				The TEA platform is available as a research preview and
				continues to evolve with community input. For more information
				or to access the platform, you can:
			</p>
			<ul class="mb-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-lg text-slate-600">
				<li>
					Visit the <a
						href="https://assuranceplatform.azurewebsites.net/"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer">TEA Platform website</a
					>
				</li>
				<li>
					Explore the <a
						href="https://alan-turing-institute.github.io/AssurancePlatform"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer">documentation site</a
					>
				</li>
				<li>
					Access the <a
						href="https://github.com/alan-turing-institute/AssurancePlatform"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a
					> for code and development
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
